		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Transformation matrix</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>In <a href="/wiki/Linear_algebra" title="Linear algebra">linear algebra</a>, <a href="/wiki/Linear_transformation" title="Linear transformation" class="mw-redirect">linear transformations</a> can be represented by <a href="/wiki/Matrix_(math)" title="Matrix (math)" class="mw-redirect">matrices</a>. If <i>T</i> is a linear transformation mapping <b>R</b><sup><i>n</i></sup> to <b>R</b><sup><i>m</i></sup> and <i>x</i> is a <a href="/wiki/Column_vector" title="Column vector">column vector</a> with <i>n</i> entries, then</p>
<dl>
<dd><img class="tex" alt="T( \vec x ) = \mathbf{A} \vec x" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/a/b/dab2db3ec1f26abb1e357212d0c9a242.png" /></dd>
</dl>
<p>for some <i>m</i>×<i>n</i> matrix <b>A</b>, called the <b>transformation matrix of <i>T</i></b>.</p>
